#A traditional PING uses ICMP and request/reply messages to verify connectivity between two devices over an IP network. 
#But what if a firewall or the device itself is blocking the PING messages? 
#What can be done? Have no fear, hping3 is here!
#How TCP and/or UDP options can be used to verify reachability and round-trip time between two devices, even when ICMP isn't allowed.
